hopobject.body: Where are you calling from? imigran online The report attributes lack of access to primary care as responsible for insufficient health outcomes and high medical costs. If everyone received the same level of care that the wealthiest residents in top-performing states receive, the report states, then an estimated 86,000 fewer people would die prematurely, 33,000 more infants born to low-income mothers would survive to see their first birthday, and more than 33 million more low-income adults and children would have health insurance.
